Divorce in Republic of Congo

Rates of divorce in Republic of Congo (in the past years, officially confirmed cases of divorce inquired for information. Thus, the number of divorces unregistered and conducted in the community represents an uncertain, larger value.) in the 60s accounted for 2-4% (3% according to some studies), in late and early 70s have increased to 56% (!), and then began to decline until the early 90s, to stand at a level of 24-28%. 4-6% of divorce cases have occurred as the results of collaboration between spouses who want to live separated.

The pace of divorce rates in Republic of Congo has slowed down for the past decade and the official divorce rate is only 3,9%. Still, many marriages still are unsuccessful and have information about unregistered marriage. In this case, marriage is conducted in another country (the European Union, mainly the Switzerland).

Reasons of success of marriage in Republic of Congo

About half of couples tend to divorce after work or school.

Division of responsibility for household chores (according to the official norms: household chores do men, house cleaning - women, washing dishes and clothes - women, cooking - women and men).

Sexual – and passionate approaches to solve the domestic conflicts.
